### req.query Parsing

Express automatically parses query strings into an object:

```javascript
// GET /search?q=express&type=framework
app.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  console.log(req.query);
  // { q: 'express', type: 'framework' }
});
```

### Filtering with Query Params

Build filters from query parameters:

```javascript
app.get('/products', (req, res) => {
  const filter = {};
  if (req.query.category) filter.category = req.query.category;
  if (req.query.minPrice) filter.price = { $gte: req.query.minPrice };
  // Use filter to query database
});
```

### Pagination

Standard pagination pattern:

```javascript
app.get('/users', (req, res) => {
  const page = parseInt(req.query.page) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit) || 10;
  const skip = (page - 1) * limit;
